relatable and accessible,

00:35:18.730 --> 00:35:20.680
but also all of the
stumbling blocks

00:35:20.680 --> 00:35:22.190
that entrepreneurship
is not just

00:35:22.190 --> 00:35:25.140
this linear path to success.

00:35:25.140 --> 00:35:28.180
We often are told that and it
seems like the instant rags

00:35:28.180 --> 00:35:28.990
to riches.

00:35:28.990 --> 00:35:31.460
I think more of us need
to talk about the problems

00:35:31.460 --> 00:35:32.770
and the struggles.

00:35:32.770 --> 00:35:34.710
And not only the
external struggles,

00:35:34.710 --> 00:35:37.450
but the internal
emotional ones as well.

00:35:37.450 --> 00:35:38.350
AUDIENCE: Thanks.

00:35:38.350 --> 00:35:39.240
LINDA ROTTENBERG: And
back to the question

00:35:39.240 --> 00:35:40.360
about crowdfunding.

00:35:40.360 --> 00:35:44.480
IBM and some other companies are
starting internal crowdfunding

00:35:44.480 --> 00:35:46.080
platforms for skunks.

00:35:46.080 --> 00:35:50.060
So people are actually getting
feedback-- so they all get $100

00:35:50.060 --> 00:35:52.870
and they can actually
put their money

00:35:52.870 --> 00:35:54.950
based on which of
